## Problem Statement:



Given an array arr[] consisting of integers where every integer appears twice except one unique integer.



Find the missing single digit without using any extra space.





Example:





Input:


arr[]={3,-4,-5}





Output:-





Missing Single Digit=-8







Explanation :-










As we know XOR operation between two same numbers gives zero hence when performing xor on entire list first time all pairs cancel themselves leaving just remaining unpaired digits left over after second iteration through whole sequence again but now instead comparing current item being processedwith previous oneswe compareitagainstresultsofarwhichisstoredinvariable named‘missing’ initially setatvalueoftopmostbit(i.e.,one).Finallywhenloopcompleteswewillhavefinalanswer storedinthemissing variable!





